name: Black and Blue
description: Experience an unforgettable dining adventure at Black and Blue in Amsterdam. Nestled in the heart of the city center, this top-rated restaurant serves the finest local dishes with a gourmet twist. Savour succulent steaks, fresh lobster, and a variety of mouthwatering French cuisine. Whether you're seeking a cozy spot for lunch near Anne Frank's house or planning a fine-dining experience, Black and Blue is the perfect destination. Voted as one of the best restaurants in Amsterdam, it offers an exceptional dining atmosphere that will make your visit to this vibrant city all the more memorable. Make a reservation at Black and Blue today!

name: Humphrey's
description:
Humphrey's Amsterdam heeft nog niet zo lang geleden een compleet nieuwe stijl gekregen. Opvallend zijn de prachtige authentieke bar en oude afgebikte muur in combinatie met de hippe roze muur. Het restaurantgedeelte is ronduit verrassend te noemen met de vele knusse hoekjes, mooie verlichting en prachtige kasten. De houten vloeren worden afgewisseld met Portugese tegels en het vele groen en de rode bomen zorgen voor een heerlijk parkgevoel.

De mooie ruimtes aan de achterzijde bieden plek voor in totaal 180 personen en zijn uitermate geschikt voor een bedrijfsuitje, personeelsuitje of verjaardagsdiner. Daarnaast beschikt het restaurant ook over een gezellig terras aan de Nieuwezijds Kolk, waar het tijdens de zomermaanden heerlijk toeven is.

Brau","reviewer_profile":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/101980794741615973936?hl=en-GB","review_text":"My visit to Humphrey Restaurant was truly memorable, thanks to its distinctive and cool atmosphere, characterized by lush plants and soft lighting.
The ambiance created a welcoming and relaxed vibe, making it the perfect setting for a delightful dining experience. I found the combination of plants and subdued lighting to be particularly charming and unique.
As for the food, while the offerings include items typically found in fast-food joints such as fries and nuggets, they were surprisingly well-prepared and flavorful. However, it's worth noting that such choices might seem a bit limited for a restaurant of this caliber.
On the beverage side, the wine selection was excellent, with some notable Italian options that added a touch of sophistication to the meal.
The service was top with a young and attentive staff ensuring that every aspect of the dining experience was taken care of.
In conclusion, I highly recommend Humphrey Restaurant for its unique ambiance, tasty food, excellent wine selection and attentive service. name: The Pantry
description: Traditionele en huisgemaakte gerechten uit de Nederlandse keuken. Bij The Pantry proeft u hoe de Nederlandse keuken smaakt. Wij serveren verse, huisgemaakte gerechten gebaseerd op traditionele recepten. Kom oer-Hollands lunchen of dineren in onze huiskamersfeer of op ons terras. Proef onze Nederlandse wijn uit de Gelderse Achterhoek. Proost met een van onze lokale (speciaal) bieren. Geniet na van uw diner met een oer-Hollandse jenever of likeur. Bekijk hier onze menukaart.

name: Restaurant Olijfje
description:
OVER ONS
Bij mediterraan restaurant Olijfje wacht de liefhebbers van mals vlees, verse vis en overheerlijke wijnen een warme en typische mediterraan gastvrijheid. Tevens kunt u genieten van onze ijskoude Spaanse bier "Mahou" van de tap.
Restaurant Olijfje is niet zomaar een restaurant, maar een complete en onvergetelijke beleving in een sfeervolle ambiance. Bij Olijfje wordt de gast nog in de watten gelegd. Terwijl de chefkok de door u gekozen gerechten klaarmaakt op een echte houtskoolgrill en u culinair verrast, kunt u genieten van onze overheerlijke zelfgemaakte Spaanse tapas en de mediterrane mezes. Humus, tzatziki, bladerdeegrolletjes met Turkse feta kaas, de Griekse dolmas en de gepanneerde gamba's zullen uw tong strelen.

name: Restaurant Zaza's
description:
Restaurant Zaza's, owned by Susie Roche from Ireland, opened its doors in May 2003 in the heart of "De Pijp", Amsterdam's Latin Quarter and hot spot for socialising. Susie and her team - Chef Cook Dave, Jasper, Noury, Ice, Gustavs and Jonah have a passion for their work and share a love of good food and great service.

Zaza's is a small, intimate restaurant with just 12 tables, serving an International menu of fresh, homemade culinary delights with influences from France, The Mediterranean and Asia which changes with the seasons.

name: Restaurant Black
description: Discover the culinary gem that is Restaurant Black, nestled in the vibrant heart of Amsterdam city center. Serving the best breakfast, lunch, and dinner near you, it's a must-visit spot for food-lovers. Looking for the best steak in Amsterdam? Your search ends at the doors of Restaurant Black. We also specialize in fine dining, offering an exquisite Lobster experience that will tantalize your taste buds. Located in the bustling Leidseplein, we're not just another restaurant - we're the best restaurant in Amsterdam. So whether you're craving a hearty breakfast, a leisurely lunch, or a decadent dinner, Restaurant Black has got you covered.

We didn't wait long for the food to arrive. The portions are large, you wouldn't need any extras with them. All freshly done and taste very nice.

We arrived at the right time for lunch, it suddenly started to get busy. A good range of choices on the menu.

Brussel Sprouts, Beef and Mushrooms Bruschettas were tasty but nothing special.

name: Deyacos Restaurant & Bar
description:
Welcome to Restaurant Deyacos! We're all about serving delicious food that makes you feel right at home. Our chefs put their hearts into every dish, using fresh, top-quality ingredients to whip up meals that are as tasty as they are beautiful.

Whether you're in the mood for something light and fresh or craving a hearty, comforting meal, we've got you covered. From our signature seafood dishes to our perfectly cooked steaks, there's something for everyone to enjoy. Come on in and find your new favorite dish!

Both burgers were cooked perfectly, and the fries were crispy and flavorful. The truffle and parmesan fries were a great addition to the Argentinian burger, and the honey mustard sauce on the chicken burger was perfectly sweet and tangy.

Deyacos also has a very cool atmosphere. The restaurant is decorated in a hip, neon-lit style, and there's a lively atmosphere.

The service was excellent. Our waiter was very attentive and made sure that we had everything we needed. He was also very knowledgeable about the menu and was able to make helpful recommendations.

The value for money was excellent. The burgers were large and filling, and the fries were a generous portion. The prices were also very reasonable.

Overall, I had a wonderful dining experience at Deyacos Restaurant & Bar. I would definitely recommend it to anyone looking for a great meal in Amsterdam.

name: Spaghetteria
description: Bent u op zoek naar een uitstekend restaurant in Amsterdam? Verwen uw smaakpapillen bij Spaghetteria, een van de beste eetgelegenheden in Amsterdam. Als een lokale favoriet, biedt Spaghetteria een authentieke en onvergetelijke culinaire ervaring. Of u nu een echte foodie bent, op zoek bent naar een plek voor fijn dineren of gewoon wilt genieten van traditioneel Nederlands eten, Spaghetteria is de place to be. Onze Amsterdamse hotspot is bekend om het serveren van de meest verrukkelijke pasta's en is een must-visit voor elke culinaire liefhebber. Ontdek waarom we worden beschouwd als een van de top Amsterdamse restaurants. Proef de heerlijke smaken van Spaghetteria vandaag nog!

name: The Lobby Nesplein
description:
The Lobby Nesplein is a popular restaurant in the heart of Amsterdam serving breakfast, lunch, brunch, and dinner in a beautiful but casual setting. Our emphasis is on fresh, quality ingredients, a frequently changing menu, and friendly but genuine service. You can also stop in for a coffee on our terrace, a cocktail with a friend, or just a wine as you watch the world go by on one of Amsterdam's oldest streets. Our motto is: "Food, Drinks, Gezelligheid". Because after all, in life, what more is there?

Want to make sure to secure a spot? Make a reservation via our website.

name: The Chicken Bar
description:
The Chicken Bar Amsterdam is the best chicken place in Amsterdam to enjoy rotisserie chicken, Vleminckx fries, Heineken on draft, cocktails and great service. If you are looking for a great chicken spot in Amsterdam this is the place to be. Enjoy our hot wings in Amsterdam!

De Chicken Bar is het beste kiprestaurant in Amsterdam. Als je op zoek bent naar kip in Amsterdam ben je bij ons bij het juiste adres. Geniet van onze rotisserie kip, Vlaamse friet, Heineken van de tap, cocktails en goede service.

Attentive, friendly and helpful. We couldn't ask for more. I didn't expect service to be so good considering it was a packed restaurant.

Atmosphere- interiors were so creative and heartwarming to see all the photos of mothers stuck from walls to ceiling, all different decades. That in itself is already a topic for conversation while dining.

Food - we got 2 rijstaffel (the one that had everything in it to make sure we try all the home style comfort food Dutch cuisine in one go.  While it may not have been 100% my kind of food, I would still give it 5 stars since the flavour of a foreign (to me) cuisine is mostly a matter of taste and preference. There was nothing wrong with the food, it wasn't too oily, too dry or undercooked or anything that could have been carelessness in the kitchen. This is Dutch food. It was served the way home cooking is done at a Dutch home and I'm happy I was able to experience it.

I wanted to try the ribs, they looked really good. But it was already too much for me.

*	The tagliatelle with lobster was another disappointment--the lobster was empty, leaving only pasta in tomato sauce.

To make matters worse, other guests around us voiced similar complaints about the service and food quality. It was clear that this wasn't an isolated incident.

This experience was unacceptable. Instead of celebrating New Year's Eve in a joyful and memorable way, we ended up hungry and disheartened on the streets of Amsterdam. name: Bleu
description: Discover exquisite dining at Restaurant Bleu, one of Amsterdam's top restaurants. Nestled in the charming Jordaan neighborhood, it is conveniently located near iconic landmarks like the Anne Frank House. This cozy restaurant is renowned for serving the best steaks in Amsterdam and is an unmissable spot for lobster lovers. From lunch to dinner, enjoy every meal with their wide-ranging French cuisine. Whether you're searching for a cafe, a food spot, or a restaurant near you in Amsterdam, Restaurant Bleu is an excellent choice. Experience the finest dining Amsterdam has to offer at this local gem.

Housed in a classic Amsterdam building, the restaurant exudes a cozy and inviting atmosphere.

The ambiance was delightful, and the staff were warm and welcoming. Seating is limited on the ground floor, and we climbed a steep, winding staircase to our reserved table on the second floor. While the restaurant was bustling, the service, though friendly, was notably slow.

For my main course, I ordered the Angus tenderloin, requesting it medium rare. Unfortunately, it arrived dry and closer to medium well. What I found particularly disappointing was that the steak did not come with a sauce. It had to be ordered separately--unlike my experiences in French restaurants. Instead, I had to pay extra for it, which felt odd. Dessert was a mixed experience--it was far too large, and the chocolate cake crumble was overpowering. Neither of us were able to finish it. A smaller, more balanced portion would have been preferable.

Despite these hiccups, we enjoyed a wonderful evening in good company. The food was amazing and the place was really lively, though we did start off a bit annoyed. But that didn't really spoil the whole fun evening.

On a busy Saturday night, I felt excited but also a bit mixed up. The bistro was full of energy, but we had a small problem at the start. We were sitting upstairs, kind of alone, and it took slightly more than 20 minutes just to get our drinks. This little mix-up was a bit of a letdown at first. And, trying to get a server's attention to order our food, even though they were close by, was a bit annoying.
It looked like people sitting downstairs got their orders faster.

As the night went on, any small issues we had at first were quickly forgotten because the food was just so good.

Starters
The scallops were amazing - cooked just right and came with a really tasty pillow of peas that was a nice surprise.
The smoked salmon on toast was simple but really well done, with great quality ingredients that all worked well together.

Main Courses
The French Fish Stew really stood out. It was a big, tasty mix of seafood, veggies, and a creamy sauce, and there was so much of it I couldn't even finish it all.
My partner had a Black Angus tenderloin that was just perfect - it looked great and tasted even better, especially with the peppery sauce that made it even more special.

Dessert
The Tarte Tatin with caramel ice cream was the perfect end to a great meal. It was just the right size for sharing.

Final Thoughts
Bistro Bleu really shows off how good food and drinks can be, all in a lively and pretty place.

The slow service at the start was a small hiccup, probably because they needed more staff. And if you want your food faster, sitting downstairs might be a good idea. But honestly, the quality of the food stands out on its own, regardless of the wait.

Bistro Bleu is definitely a place you should try, with each dish feeling like it was made with a lot of attention ","published_at":"10 months ago","published_at_date":"2024-02-25T10:10:35","response_from_owner_text":null,"response_from_owner_ago":null,"response_from_owner_date":null,"review_likes_count":0,"total_number_of_reviews_by_reviewer":null,"total_number_of_photos_by_reviewer":null,"is_local_guide":false,"review_translated_text":null,"response_from_owner_translated_text":null,"review_photos":["https://lh3.ggpht.com/p/AF1QipNTnRRvgcR2pHBldthFKdxLv-i99sxWcdYGPvjP=s1024","https://lh3.ggpht.com/p/AF1QipNhDe0bGirtLBzP9liT4uccvar12u1GP1aqNXxf=s1024","https://lh3.ggpht.com/p/AF1QipOhrWL4QeTwAsyXcYp85HniIW0MsElczgcUEjh6=s1024","https://lh3.ggpht.com/p/AF1QipNdx1M_JmlnUU9Zr2b-eYN7p5J6HjTy3-Z6BfZ_=s1024","https://lh3.ggpht.com/p/AF1QipNriVxbFhb_ut5bpZfPTnyYfVO36djfQWMduGOC=s1024"]},{"review_id":"ChdDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSUNmaGIzbWdRRRAB","rating":2,"name":"Rich Gollinge","reviewer_profile":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/102121155104326895798?hl=en-GB","review_text":"We walked in and smelled sewage. name: Burger Bar
description:
Burgerbar features not only fresh and homemade sauces, toppings and bread, but also fresh beef ground daily in our own production kitchen. We choose to work only with the best quality beef whilst offering three types in order to satisfy even the most refined palates; Irish, Angus and Wagyu beef. Come and try The Real Bite!
*Please note that our kitchen closes 30 minutes before the restaurant's closing time.*

name: Spaghetteria
description:
Kitchen closes at 22:00, drinks till midnight.

Discover Spaghetteria, a top Italian restaurant in Amsterdam, perfect for food lovers seeking an authentic dining experience. Located in the heart of the city, our menu features fresh pasta, traditional sauces, and local ingredients, making it one of the best restaurants in Amsterdam. Whether you're looking for a cozy dinner or a delightful lunch, Spaghetteria offers a warm atmosphere and friendly service that will make your meal unforgettable. Explore popular restaurants in Amsterdam and indulge in the flavors of Italy at Spaghetteria - your go-to spot for delicious food in the vibrant Amsterdam dining scene. Join us today!

name: Frenzi Italian Restaurant
description: Welcome to Frenzi, a cosy Italian restaurant in the centre of Amsterdam. Located in one of the city's most picturesque spots with stunning canal views, Frenzi is the perfect destination for lovers of fresh, authentic Italian cuisine. Indulge in our expertly crafted dishes, from handmade pastas to wood-fired pizzas, all made with the finest ingredients to delight even the most refined palates. Whether you're enjoying lunch, dinner, or drinks, our warm and inviting atmosphere sets the stage for unforgettable shared moments. Discover Italian dining at its best in Amsterdam. Let Frenzi surprise you - visit us today!

The service was quick , helpful with the menu but the tables weren't cleaned before our meal.

name: A Beautiful Mess - Amsterdam
description:
Het leukste impactrestaurant in Amsterdam aan de Oosterdokskade naast het NEMO en de OBA.
Eten verbindt en is een universeel iets. Bij A Beautiful Mess ontdek je nieuwe smaken. Een Pakistaanse linzensoep, een Eritrees stoofpotje of een heerlijke Syrische salade.

name: Restaurant Black and Blue - Reguliersdwarsstraat
description: Experience the epitome of fine dining at the esteemed Restaurant Black and Blue in Reguliersdwarsstraat, a top Amsterdam restaurant. Conveniently located near the famous flower market, it's the perfect local Amsterdam restaurant for both lunch and dinner. Renowned as one of the best restaurants in Amsterdam, it offers an exquisite selection of dishes, ensuring a memorable dining experience. For steak lovers, it's a paradise, making it the best meat restaurant in Amsterdam. Additionally, seafood enthusiasts will relish their succulent lobster. With its cozy ambiance and impressive wine list, it's the ultimate destination to wine and dine in Amsterdam. Don't miss out, book your spot now!

[{"review_id":"ChZDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSUQzOE1MalJnEAE","rating":2,"name":"Andre Slagter","reviewer_profile":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/110914088960412717920?hl=en-GB","review_text":"For the price it is not worth it.

The starter was average.
The pasta carbonara was cold, the taste of the first plate was good, but because it was cold it was sent back to the kitchen.

name: Loetje
description:
In hartje Amsterdam, tegenover Amsterdam Centraal Station, kun je in het vroegere Zuid-Hollandsch Koffiehuis, Loetje Amsterdam Centraal vinden. In ons monumentale pand, ingericht met Hollandse en Delftsblauwe accenten, kun je de lekkerste biefstuk van Amsterdam komen proeven!

Zeg je Loetje, dan zeg je de lekkerste biefstuk. Op no-nonsense wijze in echte Loetje Jus met witbrood, een royaal portie friet en salade. Bij ons geniet je van het vertrouwde biefstukreceptuur en het warme Loetje DNA.

Naast deze klassiekers hebben we bij Loetje Amsterdam Centraal nog veel meer lekkers op de kaart. Bij ons zit je ook goed voor vis, vegetarisch en overheerlijk toetjes. Zien we je snel?

Team Loetje

name: Oh My Bun! Oudebrugsteeg
description:
We couldn't find the best burgers - so we created our own!

We want you to get the best burgers and enjoy them in a unique and quirky surrounding! Oh My Bun is a very unique, funky and trendy spot where you can try our famous specialty - the Smash burger among many other various options!
We believe in transparency and providing the full experience, so we have an open kitchen concept, which means you can see your food getting prepared!
We have three locations in Amsterdam so far, with two more coming soon, so wherever you are in Amsterdam, we are never too far!

name: De Nachtwacht
description: Restaurant de Nachtwacht is al meer dan 45 jaar een begrip op het hoekje van het Rembrandtplein en Thorbeckeplein. Heerlijke steaks en klassiekers in ouderwetse Amsterdamse sferen. Onze keuken is dagelijks open tot middernacht en in het weekend zelfs tot 1.00. Al ons vlees komt van de houtskoolgrill.

We started with the mixed salads, which were really lettuce, a few cherry tomatoes, red onion and cucumber. It had a light vinaigrette. We ordered the escargot (snails) in garlic butter - so flavorful! The snails were maybe a little on the small side but excellent.

We also had the 10 oz filet- we ordered it medium rare and it might have been slightly redder than normal, but the seasoning and steak were fantastic. It came with a hollandaise sauce which was terrific, and a yellow curry that was subtle and not overwhelming. We also ordered the chimichurri and pepper sauces. Both were good, but didn't add to the steak.

The service was good. Great meal!","published_at":"4 months ago","published_at_date":"2024-09-08T16:38:40","response_from_owner_text":"Hi Mary,

Thank you for your wonderful review! We are thrilled to hear that you enjoyed your experience at Restaurant De Nachtwacht. Our team works hard to serve our guests the best meal during their trip to Amsterdam, and it's fantastic to know that this is appreciated. We look forward to welcoming you back soon for more delicious dishes and pleasant moments.

See you soon!
Team De Nachtwacht

name: Restaurant Lavash
description: Bij Lavash kun je traditionele mediteraanse gerechten combineren met moderne gerechten van nu. De tijd staat niet stil dus Lavash ook niet. Spannende cocktails en culinaire creaties in mediterrane sferen. Gezond en lekker eten staan centraal, de service en uitstraling maken de belevenis compleet. Lavash restaurant is een trendy restaurant en cocktailbar in het centrum van Amsterdam. Hopelijk tot snel!

name: Gauchos Grill Restaurant Amsterdam- Spuistraat
description:
Ontdek de verleidelijke smaken van de Argentijnse keuken bij
Gauchos Grill Restaurant op het levendige Spui in Amsterdam.
 

Gauchos is een no-nonsense steakhouse, what you see is what you get!

Met trots serveren wij Argentijns Aberdeen Angus rundvlees,
wereldwijd geroemd vanwege de topkwaliteit,
sappigheid en bijzonder karakteristieke smaak.

Laat je betoveren door de onmiskenbare geur van perfect gegrilde Argentijnse steaks

en geniet van een warme en gastvrije sfeer.

 

Of je nu komt voor een intiem diner of een gezellige avond met vrienden,

bij Gauchos Spui staat een onvergetelijke culinaire ervaring op je te wachten.

Reserveer nu je tafel en beleef de magie van Gauchos! Zomers ook op het terras

Everytime I walked by there was a big queue. So I waited for the last day in the afternoon and got in straight away. Cooked with lightening is spot on. Beautiful egg noodles, light spice and I got beef with broccoli. They add in some bean sprouts, green shallot and carrot too. Everything is cooked perfectly. I asked the male chef his recommendation for the sauce and he was so happy I did that. Trust your chef, they will guide you to a food coma. Thanks from an Aussie tourist. Come here guys, they know what they are doing. Limited seats is no problem there's spaces outside on the bridge to eat, which is what I did. The taste of their noodles is undoubtedly one of the best in town, leaving a lasting impression on your taste buds.

One of the notable aspects of Wok to Walk is their quick service. There is virtually no wait time, allowing you to satisfy your hunger promptly. The staff members are efficient and work diligently to prepare your order without delay.

While the restaurant itself may have limited seating with only two tables outside, the beauty of Amsterdam is that you can take your noodles and find a scenic spot by the canal. This allows you to enjoy the flavors served while taking in the picturesque surroundings and immersing yourself in the unique atmosphere of the city.

The variety of ingredients and sauces available at Wok to Walk is impressive. You have the freedom to customize your dish, selecting from an array of fresh vegetables, protein options, and flavorful sauces. This ensures that your noodles are tailored to your personal preferences, making each bite a delightful experience.

The portion sizes are generous, providing you with a satisfying meal that leaves you feeling full and content. The affordability of the menu is also worth mentioning, as Wok to Walk offers excellent value for the quality and quantity of food provided.

In conclusion, Wok to Walk in Amsterdam is a must-visit for noodle lovers. [{"review_id":"ChZDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSURyMzktLUZnEAE","rating":5,"name":"Chlochlo","reviewer_profile":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/107008237090006150442?hl=en-GB","review_text":"My husband and I had great time. We had a late lunch. I was craving some dumplings so their momo was perfect.
Chicken stew was yummy as well.
Pork Choila was a bit greasy but it is what it is.

We started with the artichoke and prawn croquettes, which were a wonderful balance of flavors and textures, setting the tone for the rest of the meal. For mains, we had the beef, cod, pea ravioli, and steak tartare. Each dish was beautifully presented, showcasing fresh ingredients and classic techniques. The simplicity of the food allows the quality to really shine.

The venue itself is truly something special. Housed in an old water pumping factory, the restaurant's high ceilings and preserved factory equipment give it a striking industrial-chic vibe. name: Bistro Baret
description:
Bistro Baret is een moderne bistro met een unieke ligging om de hoek bij theater Carre, met uitzicht op de artiesteningang en de Amstel. Het is een gezellig restaurant waar theatergasten en buurtbewoners samenkomen voor een heerlijke maaltijd en een gezellige borrel. Geniet van authentieke Franse gerechten in een ontspannen sfeer. Onze kaart biedt voor ieder wat wils, vlees, vis en vega. Zo kun je ook altijd bij ons gerecht voor zeevruchten en steak. We houden graag rekening met de begintijden van Carre en de theaters in de buurt, zo ben je gegarandeerd op tijd voor de aanvang van de show.
Hopelijk tot snel!

name: Onze Zaak - Italiaans Restaurant
description: Onze Zaak is een Italiaans restaurant in het hart van Amsterdam, gelegen in de pittoreske Begijnensteeg. Geniet bij ons van een verfijnde lunch, een gezellige borrel of een sfeervol diner met authentieke Italiaanse gerechten. Chef Mattia Pedroni, met ervaring in toprestaurants in Londen en New York, bereidt dagelijks vers focaccia en ravioli volgens familierecept. Met een uitgebreide wijnkaart, zorgvuldig geselecteerde lokale en biologische producten, en een fijn terras, bieden wij een complete culinaire beleving. Kom langs en proef de sfeer van Onze Zaak!

Nothing pretentious,  nothing fancy or over the top, just a simple small place where people come for a home cooked meal with simple yet high quality ingredients ( and with a helping of love for the craft of cooking).
If you get hot easily, do not come here because the restaurant does not have air conditioner and it gets stuffy.
It absolutely gave me the endearing impression of a meal at home. Creamy mushroom soup elicited nostalgic emotions.  The delicious and cooked to perfection schnitzel with a balck pepper sauce  was a celebration of quality meat. The simple sides of cooked leeks and fried ( real, not French fries) potatoes made it so much homier. For dessert , we went for the pudding of the day, which was a tapioca pudding ( not the nursing home kind, but the delicious and thick kind) with whipped cream and a liqueur-used thinl layer of sauce with have a gourmand bitterness,  toning down the sweetness.  My sister had an airy chocolate souffle ( which is exceptionally hard to make, despite the seemingly easy recipe) with a cherry preserve, sweet, yet tart.
Two things to note, you absolutely need a reservation here!!!

name: Senses Restaurant
description:
Senses is a fine dining restaurant in the city center of Amsterdam where Chef Renaud Goigoux, Sous chefs Joao Marques let their inspiration and creativity into a chefs' menu inspired by Japanese cuisine, Dutch seasonality with a French flair.

Curating the best seasonal and sustainable products of the North-sea and Dutch soil, with a focus on vegetables and seafood. The team aims to deliver the best quality of food and service to their guests with the intention to bring awareness about sustainability.

Choose from the changing 2 to 5 course lunch or 3 to 6-course dinner Chef's menu. Be guided by the five senses and go on a journey of discovery.

My partner and I recently visited this Argentinian restaurant, and while the prices were reasonable, the overall experience was far from enjoyable due to the staff's behavior.

From the moment we arrived, we felt uncomfortable. The staff repeatedly stared at us, to the point where it felt like they were sizing us up. Before our food arrived, one staff member stood right behind my chair with his hand on it, listening in on our private conversation, which was incredibly intrusive. To make matters worse, while we were eating, I was bizarrely told to switch to another seat for no apparent reason, further disrupting the experience.

When it came to the food, the ribs were overly sweet and sickly, and the salad looked nothing like the menu photos. While it did fill me up for the evening, the quality left much to be desired.

The final interaction was the most off-putting. When the bill arrived, the older waiter made a point of highlighting the tip section and seemed displeased when I chose not to add one. He sulked, walked away without thanking us, and didn't even say goodbye.

This restaurant has potential with its fair pricing and ambiance, but the staff's attitude and the food quality need serious improvement to make it a place worth recommending.","published_at":"a month ago","published_at_date":"2024-11-19T15:32:36","response_from_owner_text":null,"response_from_owner_ago":null,"response_from_owner_date":null,"review_likes_count":0,"total_number_of_reviews_by_reviewer":null,"total_number_of_photos_by_reviewer":null,"is_local_guide":false,"review_translated_text":null,"response_from_owner_translated_text":null,"review_photos":[]},{"review_id":"ChdDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSUR6NWR2SHN3RRAB","rating":2,"name":"Abu Isaac","reviewer_profile":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/115443352950219315272?hl=en-GB","review_text":"Food was lovely. name: Hemelse Modder
description: Restaurant Hemelse Modder schept de juiste voorwaarden voor mensen om met elkaar te genieten van een heerlijke maaltijd. Om vriendschap te vieren en relaties te versterken. Om iemand in het zonnetje te zetten of te bedanken. Om een gouden randje te geven aan een doordeweekse dag. Om het weekend op te tillen. Ons team zet zich in om onze gasten een mooie avond te geven. Het plezier van een goed geslaagde avond, voor iedereen aan tafel, staat centraal. In een gezellige sfeer - midden in het centrum, maar op fijne afstand van de drukte - serveren we 3, 4 en 5 gangen menu's. Elk gerecht is zorgvuldig bereid en veelal eenvoudig aan persoonlijke wensen aan te passen.

name: FuLu
description:
FuLu Mandarijn is one of the best restaurants in Amsterdam for lunch or dinner dining, thanks to our authentic Sichuan cuisine.

Chinese food can be savoured in the centre of Amsterdam, right next to Dam square, where we conjure up a wide extension of Asian food, creative desserts and signature cocktails.

Let's bring it on and enjoy the best Chinese restaurant in Amsterdam!

The flavor was a perfect balance of sweet, sour, and slightly spicy, with so much depth--it was such a perfect match with rice that I finished a bowl in no time!

I come to Fulu every time to celebrate birthdays, festivals, and friends' graduations. I still remember the first time I came to Fulu for dinner was last winter. The academic pressure made me miss home, and my friend invited me to eat at Fulu. When I opened the door on the first floor, it was almost full of Chinese people, and the smell of Chinese food made me feel like I was back home. When I looked at the menu, I felt like I wanted to eat everythingAfter the dishes were served, everyone stopped talking and started to eat. I felt healed by the taste of home.
We ordered several dishes and I recommend the following ones:
-Dry pot shrimp: The shrimp meat is full and chewy, delicious and spicy 
-Spicy chicken: Very layered, crispy on the outside and tender on the inside, the taste of pepper makes me want to eat it unstoppably
-Fish-fragrant eggplant: Although I occasionally make it myself, I still ordered it. It is completely different from making it with flavor packets. It is unexpectedly delicious and really amazing to eat with rice
-Twice-cooked pork: The surface is shiny and slightly burnt. The meat is soft and chewy when eaten. It is fat but not greasy, lean but not dry. It is a must-order with friends every time
-Dry-fried green beans: After coming here, I found that green beans are difficult to fry and difficult to make it good taste. This green bean is perfect.
Because the restaurant is in the tourist area,  it's beside Dam square and it's at the exit of Rokin subway station, you can often see tourists coming to eat. It is really kind to see people from my motherland when I am away from homeThe waiters are also very thoughtful and attentive, and I am very happy every time I come. I think it's the best Chinese restaurant in Amsterdam. If you miss the food of your hometown, and if you want to taste authentic Chinese food, come here for a meal!","published_at":"2 months ago","published_at_date":"2024-11-05T19:53:43","response_from_owner_text":"Dear Carol J,

name: Restaurant Chez Fabrice
description:
Restaurant Chez Fabrice, is de perfecte plek voor een heerlijk diner aan de Amstel. Of je nu voorafgaand aan een show in Carre komt of gewoon gezellig wilt dineren, bij Restaurant Chez Fabrice ben je van harte welkom! Op nog geen 20 meter afstand van Carre serveren wij dagelijks heerlijke Franse en mediterraanse gerechten. Restaurant Chez Fabrice is gelegen in de voormalige Carrekelder en biedt een gezellige mix van theatergangers en buurtbewoners. We houden graag rekening met de begintijden van Carre en overige theaters in de buurt.
Ook voor private dining, (werk)borrels, feestjes of groepsdiners staan wij klaar om de mogelijkheden met je door te nemen. Daarnaast kun je ook bij ons terecht voor catering aanvragen!

name: Restaurant Watergang
description: Een intieme table d'hote met Europese kaart, in het hartje van de Amsterdamse Weteringbuurt. Kies een chef's menu en wordt verrast door de creaties van Tim van Grootheest en Mattijs Pasmans. Bijpassende wijnen worden geschonken van een compacte wijnkaart met Franse, Duitse en Italiaanse wijnen

Will absolutely go back and recommend this place, it's a hidden gem!","published_at":"a month ago","published_at_date":"2024-11-29T10:23:28","response_from_owner_text":null,"response_from_owner_ago":null,"response_from_owner_date":null,"review_likes_count":0,"total_number_of_reviews_by_reviewer":null,"total_number_of_photos_by_reviewer":null,"is_local_guide":false,"review_translated_text":null,"response_from_owner_translated_text":null,"review_photos":["https://lh3.ggpht.com/p/AF1QipMXX5l8C4ViG_p9G_la8FGkL8HWNovDqH6o9yZl=s1024","https://lh3.ggpht.com/p/AF1QipPrI-poFrq2SFTr6cG6_NupoeE2vNQGkgDWes4U=s1024","https://lh3.ggpht.com/p/AF1QipMkxp1jFqcAhvchpzpQk_KfJ6e7-4GBBR30Qbp6=s1024","https://lh3.ggpht.com/p/AF1QipO8Ml3votSeKx7PiCzLWyHCL7Jve5Xvc1O-UChf=s1024","https://lh3.ggpht.com/p/AF1QipOwJ4enOr59KI1jQKAJ9ly6MmwvWjTpNx2wDvit=s1024","https://lh3.ggpht.com/p/AF1QipOYdL7Ws6M9PW1GSg5dCaovmcqzFaDwdpvDHWXO=s1024","https://lh3.ggpht.com/p/AF1QipNXOXLUQUBWJwDCLIvunTkA28cZiIMV3gnIAcNn=s1024","https://lh3.ggpht.com/p/AF1QipM7iJ-gZwJrR80z2ZeQqodPQ5NN9y64yqP2ZSPH=s1024","https://lh3.ggpht.com/p/AF1QipOWWZHUpOaEA2WLZK39A0Gqc4gDXq75pEZDZ-Kh=s1024"]},{"review_id":"ChZDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSUNueHVENFV3EAE","rating":4,"name":"Aysun Urhan","reviewer_profile":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/117383233918103919725?hl=en-GB","review_text":"A charming, cozy and casual spot for dinner. Watergang is currently one of my favorite places in Amsterdam for no fuss, high quality food.

They offer a 5 course surprise menu which changes according to the season. Every dish is well-thought where each component is in harmony. There's no fancy chef tricks just for the sake of it. You can also ask for a wine pairing or pick something from their extensive wine menu, which includes a variety of options from different parts of the world. Since their menu changes, I can't comment on a particular dish, but from our recent visit, the most memorable plate was the sous vide pork belly with smoked eel. I never thought pork belly could be that light! Of course, there's also their pillow-soft brioche bread you just want to bury your head in.

The atmosphere is very charming with cozy lighting, soft music playing in the background. It's an ideal spot for a date night or a nice dinner with friends. We were especially happy with the service, the staff is attentive and kind, they're knowledgeable about the menu and wine. The service is also fast.

Service is great, atmosphere is nice, relatively quiet place.
We paid around 300 for 2 people dinner, 5 courses with wine pairing. Genuinely enjoy it a lot!

Regarding what could have been better, 2 main points,

name: Restaurant Black Olive
description:
In ons restaurant serveren wij heerlijke mediterrane gerechten! Onze gerechten bestaan uit eerlijke en verantwoorde producten en zijn bereid in heerlijke olijfolie!
Indien u glutenvrije- of lactosevrije gerechten wilt eten is dat ook mogelijk. Heeft u andere allergieen of voorkeuren waar wij rekenging mee dienen te houden, meld het bij de bediening of tijdens uw reservering.
Naast de heerlijke gerechten heeft ons restaurant ook een nieuw luchtzuiveringssysteem. Door dit systeem wordt de lucht vier keer gefilterd, waardoor deze bacterie- en virusvrij is!
We zijn goed bereikbaar want parkeren kan onder het restaurant in parkeergarage Markenhoven. Of met OV goed bereikbaar.
Wij heten u graag welkom in Black Olive! Tot snel!

name: Restaurant Asmara
description:
Restaurant Asmara is the place to be in Amsterdam. We serve authentic Eritrean and Ethiopian Gluten Free Vegan and non-vegan dishes with less fat and with a lot of LOVE. Our Injera/'enejaraa is made from Teff. A Gluten Free Injera/'enejaraa.
Restaurant Asmara is the place to be in Amsterdam. Wij serveren authentieke Eritrese en Ethiopische glutenvrije veganistische en niet-veganistische gerechten met minder vet en met veel LIEFDE. Onze Injera/'enejaraa is gemaakt van Teff. Een Glutenvrij Injera/'enejaraa.

My recent visit to Grizzy was truly memorable, starting with their classic burger-- in my opinion the best burger in Amsterdam. It was cooked exactly as I had requested, and the blend of well chosen ingredients struck the perfect balance between robust flavour and delightful simplicity. The creamy cheese and the crisply toasted, slightly sweet bun elevated the whole experience.

The seasonal beer, a Belgian-style Ambre ale currently on offer, with its slightly dry flavour profile, was an excellent match for the meal. The selection changes seasonally, ensuring there's always something new to try out. Although initially disappointed by the unavailability of local Damrak gin, the Hendrick's gin and tonic served was flawless in mix and presentation, achieving an appealing balance without being overdone.

The window seat provided a vibrant view of Amsterdam life, a city that brings diverse people together. The bar's atmosphere, with its mix of 80s and 90s pop and rock and sports screenings, is perfect for a relaxed meal with a partner or friend. Additionally, the bar's policy on not accommodating large groups preserved the peace, and the staff's tactful management of such situations ensured everyone left in good spirits.

Grizzly American Bar is a gem, ideal for those looking to enjoy superbly crafted food and drink in a friendly and inviting setting.","published_at":"8 months ago","published_at_date":"2024-05-10T18:57:13","response_from_owner_text":null,"response_from_owner_ago":null,"response_from_owner_date":null,"review_likes_count":0,"total_number_of_reviews_by_reviewer":null,"total_number_of_photos_by_reviewer":null,"is_local_guide":false,"review_translated_text":null,"response_from_owner_translated_text":null,"review_photos":["https://lh3.ggpht.com/p/AF1QipNsJJyAhZekTs-4Cyy5zKwUNfjv-MAP45o6kPB5=s1024","https://lh3.ggpht.com/p/AF1QipNphMLjGqTKzCcOUtaXb-KyjJV1XT4dN-p5dpgI=s1024","https://lh3.ggpht.com/p/AF1QipN9UOR3RE2BH8A2q9QOk_Hu92FJaj-PlJSt3CIT=s1024","https://lh3.ggpht.com/p/AF1QipMjiw5HvtGctnDvJ1mkcIMII_uNGzYI8XJ3rDz4=s1024","https://lh3.ggpht.com/p/AF1QipPTDMGxSyEfnkJzGNCqkK0XgKYSw3n0m6cLCrrI=s1024","https://lh3.ggpht.com/p/AF1QipMkXto4k0EIiuaJjsyZxbGIIig0i059V0zFmWrq=s1024","https://lh3.ggpht.com/p/AF1QipOOE2A2s-KvSbgez3QiKG3RInWIvXuRFSynV0qJ=s1024"]},{"review_id":"ChdDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSUNQdUotTDZRRRAB","rating":5,"name":"claire moore","reviewer_profile":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/106779399179576151002?hl=en-GB","review_text":"Nice friendly atmosphere! name: Restaurant Red
description: Discover the tantalising flavours of the best steak in Amsterdam at Restaurant RED. Gourmet steak lovers, our premium steakhouse provides a dining experience like no other. From succulent ribeye steak to a variety of steak meals, our menu is a carnivore's dream. Not only do we excel at steak, but we're also well-renowned as a top lobster and fish restaurant in Amsterdam. Situated near the historic Rijksmuseum, whether you're looking for breakfast, lunch, dinner, or a canal-side diner, Restaurant RED is the place to be. We promise a dining experience that will keep you coming back for more. Choose Restaurant RED for the ultimate Amsterdam steakhouse experience.

description:
Van Kerkwijk is een klassiek Amsterdams cafe-restaurant.
Van Kerkwijk staat voor goed eten en drinken in een stadse sfeer.
Eigenzinnig, zonder kapsones voor een goede prijs.
Van Kerkwijk bestaat 20 jaar, nu met wat aanpassingen maar nog steeds persoonlijk en vertrouwd.

name: Restaurant Sardegna
description:
In the characteristic Cornelis Schuytstraat in the Old South you will find restaurant Sardegna. Inside or on the royal terrace with heating, for lunch or dinner, for business or private gatherings in a cosy Italian ambience.
Our products and ingredients come directly from Italy, and the pastas are made by hand in-house. We invite you into our Italian atmosphere for pizza, pasta, carne (meat) or pesce (fish).
Also try our beautiful Italian house wines, or choose from our specially selected wine menu.

We'd love to see you soon!

description:

We can't wait to welcome you soon at Klein BREDA.

name: Roberto's Restaurant Amsterdam
description: Experience classic Italian gastronomy at Roberto's Restaurant. Pure Italian cuisine inspired by original signature recipes. Roberto's will take you back to the 1960s, when people made dining an event. Our famous Italian restaurant has been a local favourite for over 30 years. Led by Executive Chef Franz Conde, Roberto's offers classic Italian dishes prepared with fresh seasonal ingredients.

The servers were nice and wanted to remedy the situation, so they offered us a coffee and tiramisu on the house. We tasted the tiramisu and it was just...I don't even have words how to describe such a bad, terrible tiramisu.

name: soupenzo - spiegel
description: Our promise is that we serve you fresh and honest food that is organic and healthy. We do this in the tradition of homemade soup, salad and bakery items. With our well-equipped kitchen we are professional, but certainly not industrial. This means that everything we do is handmade and prepared from start to finish. That gives us the opportunity to prepare food with love and care. You can see and taste that work has been done on it. We think that is super important.

The restaurant offers a variety of well-cooked steaks, with the Lomito being a popular choice among patrons.

The steak quality is very good, and the meat is cooked to perfection. The location is convenient, being close to Dam Square, which makes it an easy choice for tourists exploring the area. The staff is friendly, adding to the positive dining experience.

However, the restaurant's setting is quite simple, with basic chairs and tables. It's not a fancy place, so don't expect a luxurious ambiance. Steaks are served on their own, and you need to order sides separately. While some might prefer this, it can be a downside for those who expect a complete meal without additional charges. Additionally, the staff, while friendly, can be a bit slow, which might affect the overall dining experience.

Overall, CAU Steak Restaurant is a great choice for those looking to enjoy good steak near Dam Square. Despite its simplicity and a few drawbacks, the quality of the food makes it worth a visit.","published_at":"6 months ago","published_at_date":"2024-06-30T20:04:34","response_from_owner_text":"Hi Ziv,

name: Restaurant DenC, Dik en Cunningham
description: In de Kerkstraat, om de hoek van de Utrechtsestraat zit DenC, Dik en Cunningham. Een huiskamer-restaurant waar ambachtelijk wordt gekookt, alles wordt zelf bereid met de beste ingredienten. De keuken is gespecialiseerd in de bereiding van Hollands wild, het hele jaar door staan de mooiste wild gerechten op de kaart, naast vis, vleesgerechten.. Dagelijks kan u ook genieten van een pre-theater menu voordat uw voorstelling begint. Schuif aan tussen 17:30 en 18:30 en er wordt gezorgd dat u op tijd bij uw voorstelling bent. Het 3 gangen theater menu, inclusief koffie kost EU45,50 per persoon.

name: Restaurant Argentalia Amsterdam
description:
Argentalia is a fusion restaurant, a unique culinary blend of the flavorful traditions of Italy and Argentina. Located in the city's heart, we take our patrons on a gastronomic journey, merging the rustic charm of Argentine food with the subtlety of Italian gastronomy.

Our menu is centered around fresh ingredients and authentic recipes. It embodies the hearty Argentine flavors famous for its robust meats, with Italy's rich heritage of fresh pasta, aromatic sauces, and divine cheese and wine.
Argentalia's aesthetic reflects its menu - a beautiful amalgamation of rustic Argentine warmth and timeless Italian elegance.

name: Ashoka
description:
Fine Dining with a Refined Concept
**********************
Serving the finest Indian and Nepalese cuisines since 2013, Ashoka is ranked as one of the best restaurants in Amsterdam.

Refined service paired with caring, gracious hospitality, and soulful Indian and Nepalese cuisines at a fair price in a cozy and beautiful restaurant in the heart of Amsterdam. Enjoy and experience the amazing flavors of India and Nepal in our one-of-a-kind restaurant built in the monument warehouse.

Located in the historical heart of the city, Ashoka is just a stone's throw away from Amsterdam Central Station. Famous Dam Square and Amsterdam's leading department store De Bijenkorf are within walking distance; just 600 meters from our doorstep.

[{"review_id":"ChdDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSUNQaEx5YXd3RRAB","rating":5,"name":"Rayan Alwabil","reviewer_profile":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/104512169807719286736?hl=en-GB","review_text":"My wife and I recently had the pleasure of dining at Ashoka, and I can honestly say it was an unforgettable experience from start to finish. We booked in advance, excited to try their renowned cuisine, and were immediately impressed by the elegant ambiance of the restaurant. The decor perfectly sets the stage for a delightful evening.

We opted for the chef's tasting menu for two, and it was nothing short of amazing. Each course was thoughtfully prepared and beautifully presented, showcasing the best dishes that Ashoka has to offer. The portions were just right, allowing us to savor each flavor without feeling overwhelmed.

Among the standout dishes, the butter chicken was a true highlight. Rich and creamy, it was bursting with flavor--definitely one of the best I've ever had. We also loved the masala, which was perfectly spiced and complemented the other dishes beautifully. Every bite was a celebration of Indian cuisine, and the variety in the tasting plate kept our taste buds excited.

What truly enhanced our experience was the exceptional service. The staff were not only helpful but also genuinely friendly. They were attentive without being intrusive, making sure our dining experience was seamless and enjoyable.

Overall, our evening at Ashoka was a wonderful culinary journey that we will be talking about for a long time. We can't wait to return and explore more of their delicious offerings. Highly recommend this restaurant to anyone looking for a top-notch dining experience!","published_at":"a month ago","published_at_date":"2024-11-21T13:05:20","response_from_owner_text":"Hello. Namaste Rayan,
We are delighted that you have chosen to dine with us! We appreciate your positive feedback and look forward to continuing to provide exceptional service.

We started with the appetisers, which were decent but didn't stand out much in terms of flavour. We had Chicken Choila and Chicken Momo. The Momo were a bit of a disappointment, as they were served cold. We were expecting them to be at least warm, considering how they're typically enjoyed fresh, but they missed the mark in that regard.

However, the main course more than made up for it. The Kukhura Ko Masu (traditional Nepalese chicken curry) was absolutely on point. The flavour was rich, and well-seasoned. It was the highlight of the meal, and we really enjoyed it. It came with rice by default, and we added an extra garlic naan, which was delicious, warm, and perfectly complementing the curry.

What really made the experience stand out was the service. The staff was exceptionally friendly, attentive, and accommodating, which made us feel very welcome throughout our meal. They were definitely a big part of the positive experience.

name: Venster 33
description: Looking for a restaurant in Amsterdam? Look no further than Venster 33! Known for its delicious food and amazing cocktails, Venster 33 is the perfect spot to satisfy your cravings. Whether you're in the mood for Dutch cuisine or just want to grab a quick lunch, this place has got you covered. With its cozy atmosphere and friendly staff, you'll feel right at home. Located in the popular district of de Pijp, it's easily accessible and convenient. So, if you're searching for a restaurant in Amsterdam that serves good food and tasty cocktails, Venster 33 is your go-to spot!

name: Palmyra Syrian Restaurant
description:
Van harte welkom in ons Palmyra Restaurant .
We willen u een greep uit onze culinaire Lebanese en Midden-Oosters keuken laten proeven met echt authentieke gerechten gemaakt door onze ervaren chef kok Ibrahim Hanna Shamoun .
Bij ons is het de traditie om onze gerechten met elkaar te delen zodat u alle smaken kunt proeven uit onze geweldige keuken van Speciale Grill en vegetarische gerechten
Welkom

name: Bistrot Neuf
description: Neuf is een authentiek Frans restaurant gelegen op de bruisende Haarlemmerstraat, aan de rand van de nostalgische Jordaan in Amsterdam. Neuf staat voor ongecompliceerd en lekker eten, met als basis wijn. We serveren 7 dagen per week (warme) lunch en diner en alle gerechten worden in eigen huis bereid. Kies een van onze heerlijke a la carte gerechten of laat je verrassen door de Chef in de vorm van een 3-, 4- of 5 gangen Chefs Tasting Menu. De warme keuken is iedere dag vanaf 12:00 uur geopend voor lunch (tot 16:30 uur) en voor diner vanaf 17:30 uur tot 22:00 uur.

name: Restaurant Bellavista
description: Restaurant Bellavista is een van de leukste Italiaanse restaurants in Amsterdam. Het menu bestaat voornamelijk uit de bekende traditionele Italiaanse gerechten en ook pizza's ontbreken niet op de kaart. Dit is een restaurant waar de jarenlange ervaring te proeven is. De producten zijn vers, smaakvol en van de beste kwaliteit. De sfeer is ontspannen, het interieur adembenemend mooi, mede dankzij de verse bloemen. Gastvrijheid staat bij Bellavista voorop. Het personeel is altijd vriendelijk en zeer gastvrij.

name: De Japanner West
description: Experience the authentic flavors of Japan at De Japanner West, an exquisite Japanese restaurant located in the heart of Amsterdam. Renowned for offering the best Japanese cuisine in the city, this Asian restaurant will transport you straight to Tokyo with its traditional dishes and relaxed atmosphere. Whether you're a sushi lover or a dumpling aficionado, De Japanner West is the perfect place for your Asian food cravings. Its close proximity makes it an easy choice for those searching for "Japanese restaurant near me" or "Asian restaurant close to me." Indulge in an unforgettable dining experience at De Japanner West, one of the best Japanese and Asian restaurants in Amsterdam. See you soon!

name: Mitts Restaurant
description:
When we opened in 2019, we had a clear vision of what great food should look and taste like.

We've since perfected our passion for pure tastes with classic Eastern mediterranean flavors and source fresh, high-quality ingredients from local and organic suppliers.

But Mitts is more than food - our welcoming atmosphere and cocktail and wine menu are designed to make you feel comfortable and satisfied.

name: Restaurant & Pizzeria Lucca Due
description:
Bij Lucca Due streven we naar gezellig, lekker en kwalitatief goed Italiaans eten. We hebben een binnentuin waar je altijd gezellig, Lekker kan eten en met het mooi weer hebben we ook terras bij het Kerkplein van Posthoornkerk

Wij zijn 22 juli t/m 14 augustus gesloten. We gaan er even tussenuit

We hopen je snel eens te mogen ontmoeten.

[{"review_id":"ChdDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSUR2OGRXUWhBRRAB","rating":4,"name":"Andre Slagter","reviewer_profile":"https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/110914088960412717920?hl=en-GB","review_text":"Lumbini is a nice restaurant with an Indian/Nepalese menu.

The decoration of the restaurant could be better in my opinion.
Paper tablecloths and paper napkins look a bit cheap for a nice and atmospheric restaurant.

The service is good and attentive.
Only something probably went wrong with the spiciness.

name: Maris Piper Brasserie
description:
Maris Piper is a luxurious contemporary brasserie set on a beautiful corner of Frans Halsstraat in the vibrant De Pijp district, South Amsterdam.

Indulge in distinguished dishes from the brasserie menu in a relaxed but classy ambiance, with cosy private booths, an elegant open space, fireplace seating and a luminous conservatory with romantic tables for two.

Normally, I wouldn't get excited about bread but the smoked almond/garlic butter they pair it with is just delicious. After a while we were even offered a table seat and continued our dinner there. The food is scrumptious!

The dishes are all prepared with care and were amazing. The wine was surprisingly well-priced and our waiters each gave us amazing warm service. Our waiter Nikos had great recommendations for the food and even for a coffee place in the morning. We felt pampered all evening. I was even surprised about the desserts; sometimes it can be an afterthought, but at Maris Piper each dessert was well balanced and brought their own personality. The restaurant itself is quite nice - the location is convenient, the atmosphere is warm, and the vibe is inviting. The staff were polite, though the service lacked a certain attentiveness.

Unfortunately, the experience was overshadowed by a few key issues. Despite having a reservation at 8:15 PM and arriving on time, we were seated at 8:20 PM and didn't start eating until 10:20 PM. Waiting over two hours for food is simply unacceptable. When the dishes finally arrived, they were lukewarm, which detracted significantly from the enjoyment. For example, the onion soup had excellent flavor but was served cold, and as a result, it was hard to appreciate fully.

Another concern was the portion sizes. The onion soup was more like half a dish, not even a full serving, and the portion of fries was tiny--barely half the small container they brought to the table. For the price and presentation, the portion sizes were disappointing and left us unsatisfied.

While the restaurant has potential with its ambiance and flavors, the delays, cold food, and small portions made the overall experience underwhelming. name: Steak Club Leidse
description:
With only 97 seats, and a private chef table dining Leidse SteakClub is an intimate restaurant with high ceilings and a warm industrial design. A full bar and custom cocktail program are also included, every weekend DJs spin until late hours. promises the ultimate in a hedonistic night out.
Leidse SteakClub is open for dinner seven days a week.

description: Our promise is that we serve you fresh and honest food that is organic and healthy. We do this in the tradition of homemade soup, salad and bakery items. With our well-equipped kitchen we are professional, but certainly not industrial. This means that everything we do is handmade and prepared from start to finish. That gives us the opportunity to prepare food with love and care. You can see and taste that work has been done on it. We think that is super important.

name: Anmol restaurant
description: We are a family-owned restaurant located in the heart of Amsterdam. Since 2001, our mission has been to serve excellent food with excellent quality to all our diners. Warm smiles and welcome greetings are our number one guarantee to you. Dine-in at Anmol where you will always be treated as family! You eat here as if you were eating 7,103 kilometers away.

name: Los Pilones
description:
FROM MEXICO TO AMSTERDAM
From Mexico to Amsterdam
How it all came to be...

It all started in 2001 when Los Pilones opened the doors at Kerkstraat 63 and introduced authentic Mexican cuisine in The Netherlands!

Los Pilones is a Mexican cantina style concept, serving fresh home made food and drinks in a colourful and vibrant atmosphere - a fiesta straight from Mexico to Amsterdam. You can drop in for tacos, enchiladas, flautas, quesadillas, fresh margaritas, micheladas, over 200 different kinds of 100% agave tequilas and mezcal.

Pilon in Mexico means "a little extra" and that is exactly what we intend to give you when you visit Los Pilones!

name: Cecconi's Amsterdam
description:
Located in the 1930s Bungehuis building on the Singel canal, Cecconi's Amsterdam is a modern day classic Italian restaurant open for dinner.

Cecconi's serves hand-made pasta, seafood and dishes from Italy using the finest ingredients.

In addition to the original restaurant in Mayfair, London, Cecconi's has locations in Miami, West Hollywood, Istanbul and Berlin.

As someone familiar with the richness and tradition of Turkish food, I knew the real test of a restaurant like this would be in the quality of their meat--and Orontes De Pijp exceeded all expectations.

The mixed grill, a hallmark of any Turkish dining experience, was a standout dish. The meat was perfectly cooked: tender, juicy, and packed with flavor that highlighted the mastery of their chefs. Every bite of lamb, chicken, and beef was full of rich, authentic taste, and it was clear that careful attention had gone into marinating and grilling the meats to perfection. The balance of spices was impeccable, enhancing the natural flavors without overwhelming them.

Beyond the food, the service was warm and attentive, delivered by a staff that clearly takes pride in their craft. The passion for food and hospitality was evident in every aspect of the meal. Whether you're a seasoned lover of Turkish cuisine or new to it, Orontes De Pijp is an unforgettable experience that transports you straight to the heart of Turkey through its remarkable dishes and genuine service. name: Cantine de Caron
description: Cantine de Caron, is het grootste restauarant van de familie Caron. Gelegen midden in het hart van het historische Westerpark. In het industriele decor van dit voormalige fabrieksgebouw geniet je van klassieke Franse gerechten met een mediterraan accent, omringd door de levendigheid van het Westergasterrein. Neem plaats binnen in de warme, rauwe ambiance van het monumentale pand of op ons zonnige terras met uitzicht op het park. Of je nu op zoek bent naar een gezellige lunch in de buurt of een uitgebreid diner, bij Cantine de Caron ben je altijd welkom.

name: Day's StoneGrill 1870 | Foodbar
description: DAY'S StoneGrill 1870 is a steakhouse where you can go for lunch and dinner. The pieces of meat come from all over the world, such as Argentina, New Zealand and Canada. The menu specializes in grill dishes and also has dishes with burgers, pizzas, pastas and chicken. You can choose a side dish with every entree from DAY'S StoneGrill 1870, such as French fries, rice or vegetables. At DAY'S StoneGrill 1870's bar, all kinds of beer, wines and spirits such as vodka, rum and whiskeys are served. Here you have the option to grill as in 1870. We prepare all meat dishes perfectly from the kitchen and you can grill it at the table. If it's a nice, sunny day, you can enjoy your meal outside on the covered patio.

I had the fish and chips and my wife had the burger--both were very good (along with the beers!) and the staff was helpful and attentive.

As I said above, the only negative was the length of time to receive our main courses, about 1 hour.

I had seen another couple receive the same order we had (fish and chips, burger) and after about an hour, I was about to ask the staff about our order but before I could, our order was brought out to us.  The food was very tasty and piping hot so it was freshly prepared.

Even though we were eating well before the normal dinner time, it could have been just a surge of customers.  There were empty tables when we arrived but the place was packed when we left.

name: Cantina Caliente - Cocina Latina
description:
Our definition of cantina is a place where you can come for a coffee, lunch, dinner some snacks or just a drink.

We are specialized in Latin-American food and serve authentic dishes like hand-made blue corn tacos, Peruvian ceviche, Argentinian beef, empanadas and many vegan options.

We have an extended menu of tequilas, mezcales, pisco, wines, beers and cocktails.

name: Brasserie Ambassade
description:
Kom binnen voor een heerlijk ontbijt, lunch of diner bij Brasserie Ambassade - onderdeel van het Ambassade Hotel - gelegen aan de Herengracht in het centrum van Amsterdam. Geniet van de Franse keuken met een moderne twist terwijl je omringd wordt door kleurrijke schilderijen van bekende CoBrA kunstenaars. Of neem in de zomer plaats op ons terras met uitzicht op de gracht!

Bij Brasserie Ambassade ligt de nadruk op verse, seizoensgebonden, ambachtelijke en lokale producten. De keuken van Brasserie Ambassade biedt een heerlijk en veelzijdig a la carte menu en wijnkaart.
Het team van Brasserie Ambassade verwelkomt u graag!
